        <title>Johnson v. Home State Bank</title>
        <section startTime="0.000" stopTime="44.095">
          <heading/>
          <turn speaker="william_h_rehnquist" startTime="0.000" stopTime="8.903">
            <label>Chief Justice Rehnquist</label>
            <text syncTime="0.000" offset="73964">The opinion of the Court in No. 90-693, Johnson versus Home State Bank will be announced by Justice Marshall.</text>
          </turn>
          <turn speaker="thurgood_marshall" startTime="8.903" stopTime="44.095">
            <label>Justice Thurgood Marshall</label>
            <text syncTime="8.903" offset="109491">This case is here on certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Tenth Circuit.</text>
            <text syncTime="15.463" offset="135717">The issue is whether a mortgage lien that passes through the Chapter 7 Bankruptcy is a claim subject to inclusion in the Chapter 13 reorganization plan.</text>
            <text syncTime="30.137" offset="194441">In an opinion filed with the Clerk today, we hold that a mortgage lien, in such circumstances, is a claim under the Bankruptcy Code.</text>
            <text syncTime="39.653" offset="232475">We, therefore, reverse the judgment of the Tenth Circuit.</text>
          </turn>
        </section>
